<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>The @@@D2Smite@@@r Paladin is the strongest and easiest class used for soloing Uber Tristram. With a strong single target stunning attack that never misses and a high Life total replenished by Lifetap, the @@@D2Smite@@@r can take down the Ubers or any boss with extremely budget gear. While he is extremely good at single target killing, he does suffer from no area of effect skill which limits his overall kill speed in crowded areas.</p>

<h1>Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Skill Build</h2>

<p>The following section shows the core skills for the @@@D2Smite@@@r. For a detailed breakdown of all core and optional skills as well as the recommended order for allocating skill points, refer to the Skills section of this guide.</p>

<ol>
<li>1 point to all prerequisites</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Smite@@@ - Max immediately, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2HolyShield@@@ - Place a couple of points immediately for duration and then max after @@@D2Smite@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Fanaticism@@@ - First point at 30 and then wait to max until after @@@D2HolyShield@@@, required</li>
</ol>

